{
  "texts": [
    "Naive Bayes:The Naive Bayes model exhibited an accuracy of 82.347%.",
    "This probabilistic classifier, based on Bayes' Theorem, assumes conditional independence between features.",
    "While Naive Bayes is efficient and straightforward, its assumption of feature independence can be a limitation in capturing the complex and often interdependent nature of sentiment in text data.",
    "Extreme Gradient Boosting (XGBoost):XGBoost achieved an accuracy of 91.511%.",
    "Known for its effectiveness in various machine learning tasks, XGBoost benefits from its gradient boosting framework, which incrementally improves model performance by focusing on errors made by previous models."
  ]
}